Package fi.tuni.tamk.tiko.objectorientedprogramming

Class JSONObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • fi.tuni.tamk.tiko.objectorientedprogramming.JSONObject
  • public class JSONObject
extends Object
    Class from which objects containing json key and value data can be created. The class contains two lists for keys and values.
    Version:
    2019.1612
    Author:
    Lassi Markkinen

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put​(String key,
                Object value)
        Method for inserting a key and value pair into the JSONObject. A try-catch block is used to potential JSONObjectExceptions regarding duplicate keys. if no duplicates are found the key and value are added to the JSONObject.
        Parameters:
        key - Key to insert.
        value - Value to insert.

      • getKey

        public String getKey()
        Utility method for returning the first value in the keys list. This is used in the shopping list application by the TableColumns to display item names to the user.
        Returns:
        The first value in the keys array.

      • getValue

        public String getValue()
        Utility method for returning the first value in the values list. This is used in the shopping list application by the tableColumns to display item amounts to the user.
        Returns:
        The first value in the values array.
